<subSubSection id="23F41BEAFF89202524EB64C6A5AB1C39" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="586" pageId="3" pageNumber="585" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="6B514861FF89202224EB64C6A2831AAC" blockId="3.[151,1436,1864,2035]" box="[199,1436,2007,2035]" pageId="3" pageNumber="585">
<emphasis id="599A9473FF89202224EB64C6A65D1AAC" bold="true" box="[199,322,2007,2034]" pageId="3" pageNumber="585">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body has conspicuous fine and long hairs on dorsal surface, hairs as long as or longer than two dis-
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6B514861FF8E202524BB6388A5AB1C39" blockId="4.[151,1437,153,1223]" pageId="4" pageNumber="586">
tal antennomeres. Dense and shorter pubescence on ventral surface. Antennae generally have four dilated preapical antennomeres (
<figureCitation id="F3D554E4FF8E2025256E63ACA68B1D89" box="[322,404,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1960,1985]" captionTargetBox="[158,1428,1312,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,1305,1889]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Arthrobrachus longipilis. a: Antenna. Terminal segments of abdomen: b: v: V ventrite, vi: VI ventrite, lt: last tergite and fla: flange; c: IX segment. Scale 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3714637" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3714637/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="586">Fig. 4a</figureCitation>
); pronotum has rounded distal and basal angles; ventrite 6 has a single transverse plate (
<figureCitation id="F3D554E4FF8E2025214363ACA7A81DA2" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1960,1985]" captionTargetBox="[158,1428,1312,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,1305,1889]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Arthrobrachus longipilis. a: Antenna. Terminal segments of abdomen: b: v: V ventrite, vi: VI ventrite, lt: last tergite and fla: flange; c: IX segment. Scale 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3714637" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3714637/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="586">Fig. 4b</figureCitation>
); last tergite is elongated, posterior edge has a projected flange on the inner face (
<figureCitation id="F3D554E4FF8E2025207D63F0A3BA1DA2" box="[1105,1189,225,252]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1960,1985]" captionTargetBox="[158,1428,1312,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,1305,1889]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Arthrobrachus longipilis. a: Antenna. Terminal segments of abdomen: b: v: V ventrite, vi: VI ventrite, lt: last tergite and fla: flange; c: IX segment. Scale 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3714637" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3714637/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="586">Fig. 4b</figureCitation>
), with dense and long hairs; parameres are slightly sclerotized, narrow lateral edges, linear at apex (
<figureCitation id="F3D554E4FF8E202527DA6214A3571C41" box="[1014,1096,260,287]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="5.[151,250,873,898]" captionTargetBox="[162,1427,174,843]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,174,854]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 5. Arthrobrachus longipilis. Male genitalia. Tegmen and parameres: a: dorsal view; p: parameres; b: lateral view; Median lobe: c: dorsal view, ap: apodeme, pha: phallotreme,; d: ventral view; e: lateral view. Scale 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3714639" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3714639/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="586">Fig. 5a</figureCitation>
); tegmen has no dorsal flange, tegminal plate is reduced and flat, narrow tegminal arms, convergent in the basal area (
<figureCitation id="F3D554E4FF8E2025207E6238A3BC1C1D" box="[1106,1187,296,323]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="5.[151,250,873,898]" captionTargetBox="[162,1427,174,843]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,174,854]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 5. Arthrobrachus longipilis. Male genitalia. Tegmen and parameres: a: dorsal view; p: parameres; b: lateral view; Median lobe: c: dorsal view, ap: apodeme, pha: phallotreme,; d: ventral view; e: lateral view. Scale 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3714639" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3714639/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="586">Fig. 5a</figureCitation>
); median lobe is thick, subcylindrical, with no flection area (
<figureCitation id="F3D554E4FF8E20252616625CA5641C39" box="[570,635,332,359]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="5.[151,250,873,898]" captionTargetBox="[162,1427,174,843]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,174,854]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 5. Arthrobrachus longipilis. Male genitalia. Tegmen and parameres: a: dorsal view; p: parameres; b: lateral view; Median lobe: c: dorsal view, ap: apodeme, pha: phallotreme,; d: ventral view; e: lateral view. Scale 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3714639" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3714639/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="586">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
c–e).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="23F41BEAFF8E202524EB6261A5AB1905" pageId="4" pageNumber="586" type="description">
<paragraph id="6B514861FF8E202524EB6261A24D1C8D" blockId="4.[151,1437,153,1223]" pageId="4" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis id="599A9473FF8E202524EB6261A64E1CD5" bold="true" box="[199,337,368,395]" pageId="4" pageNumber="586">Description</emphasis>
: Male: body length 
<quantity id="AC16E584FF8E202526126260A59B1CD5" box="[574,644,369,395]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="586" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
, length: width ratio as 1.25:1, sides subparallel; pronotum and elytra with distinct coarse punctures; pubescence fine, with hairs as long or longer than two distal antennomeres, dense on dorsal surface, dense and shorter on ventral surface; body dark testaceous, antennae and legs light testaceus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6B514861FF8E202524EB62CCA3CC1F45" blockId="4.[151,1437,153,1223]" pageId="4" pageNumber="586">
Head: Including the eyes, slightly wider than the distal margin of the pronotum (1.1:1); antennae shorter than the length of the pronotum (0.75:1), with four dilated, rounded preapical antennomeres (
<figureCitation id="F3D554E4FF8E202520586110A3D91F45" box="[1140,1222,513,539]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1960,1985]" captionTargetBox="[158,1428,1312,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,1305,1889]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Arthrobrachus longipilis. a: Antenna. Terminal segments of abdomen: b: v: V ventrite, vi: VI ventrite, lt: last tergite and fla: flange; c: IX segment. Scale 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3714637" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3714637/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="586">Fig. 4a</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6B514861FF8E202524EB6134A53B1E49" blockId="4.[151,1437,153,1223]" pageId="4" pageNumber="586">Thorax: Pronotum wider than it is long (1.7:1), moderately convex transversely and slightly curved longitudinally, the base as wide as the apex (1:1) and narrower than the humeral region (0.8:1), from a dorsal view the distal margin is slightly convex, distal and basal margins are well marked, lateral margins are slightly curved; distal and basal angles are rounded. Elytra 1.9:1 longer than it is wide; lateral margins are subparallel in the two basal thirds and rounded in the distal one; disc is moderately convex, with light lateral border; epipleura are narrow, grainy and hairy, with small apical denticles. Legs: median and hind tibiae with scarce and small spines in the external margin, tarsomeres with few ventral spines.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6B514861FF8E202524EB6030A5AB1905" blockId="4.[151,1437,153,1223]" pageId="4" pageNumber="586">
Abdomen: Ventrite 5 with distal margin convex laterally, projected medially and with an emargination at center; ventrite 6 not divided well emarginated at center; last tergite is elongated, posterior margin almost straight with a projected flange on the inner face (
<figureCitation id="F3D554E4FF8E202526316078A56F1EDA" box="[541,624,873,900]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1960,1985]" captionTargetBox="[158,1428,1312,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,1305,1889]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Arthrobrachus longipilis. a: Antenna. Terminal segments of abdomen: b: v: V ventrite, vi: VI ventrite, lt: last tergite and fla: flange; c: IX segment. Scale 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3714637" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3714637/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="586">Fig. 4b</figureCitation>
), as long as a third of the length of the tergite, with dense and long hairs; segment 9 is sclerotized, with a narrow tergum, fine sternal arms and a short apodeme (
<figureCitation id="F3D554E4FF8E2025205C609CA3DC1EF9" box="[1136,1219,909,935]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1960,1985]" captionTargetBox="[158,1428,1312,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,1305,1889]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Arthrobrachus longipilis. a: Antenna. Terminal segments of abdomen: b: v: V ventrite, vi: VI ventrite, lt: last tergite and fla: flange; c: IX segment. Scale 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3714637" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3714637/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="586">Fig. 4c</figureCitation>
). Genitalia: parameres slightly sclerotized, narrow lateral edges curved, communicated at apex with a linear sclerite, in a straight line with the arms of the tegmen (
<figureCitation id="F3D554E4FF8E202525C460C4A5461EAE" box="[488,601,980,1008]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="5.[151,250,873,898]" captionTargetBox="[162,1427,174,843]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,174,854]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 5. Arthrobrachus longipilis. Male genitalia. Tegmen and parameres: a: dorsal view; p: parameres; b: lateral view; Median lobe: c: dorsal view, ap: apodeme, pha: phallotreme,; d: ventral view; e: lateral view. Scale 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3714639" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3714639/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="586">Fig. 5 a,b</figureCitation>
); tegmen without dorsal flange, tegminal plate reduced and flat, tegminal arms narrow, convergent at the base; apodeme reduced (
<figureCitation id="F3D554E4FF8E2025272660E8A46E194D" box="[778,881,1016,1043]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="5.[151,250,873,898]" captionTargetBox="[162,1427,174,843]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,174,854]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 5. Arthrobrachus longipilis. Male genitalia. Tegmen and parameres: a: dorsal view; p: parameres; b: lateral view; Median lobe: c: dorsal view, ap: apodeme, pha: phallotreme,; d: ventral view; e: lateral view. Scale 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3714639" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3714639/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="586">Fig. 5a,b</figureCitation>
); median lobe body, sclerosed, thick, subcylindrical, no flection area at the base; phallotreme oval; apex acuminated at center; in lateral view, strongly curved at base; apodeme is wide and open ventrally (
<figureCitation id="F3D554E4FF8E202526166750A5641905" box="[570,635,1088,1115]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="5.[151,250,873,898]" captionTargetBox="[162,1427,174,843]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,174,854]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 5. Arthrobrachus longipilis. Male genitalia. Tegmen and parameres: a: dorsal view; p: parameres; b: lateral view; Median lobe: c: dorsal view, ap: apodeme, pha: phallotreme,; d: ventral view; e: lateral view. Scale 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3714639" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3714639/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="586">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
c–e).
</paragraph>
